Suppress the native travel destination window (GM_Travel) when Travel is in DS mode, so the
companion (bottom-screen) travel overlay is the sole surface; show the native window when Travel is
Vanilla. Companion to companion-travel-export.patch, and the same mechanism as the six
mGuiModeStates windows in companion-hide-gamewindows-on-dsmode.patch.

TravelWindow is NOT a WindowManager member (there is no mTravelWindow) — it lives only in
mGuiModeStates[GM_Travel].mWindows — so it can't use the member-setVisible form the barter/dialogue
patches use; iterate the mode's windows exactly like that switch. Kept as its own patch (not a case
in that switch) so it applies independently: hunk 1 adds a namespace-scope `extern "C" bool
companionDsTravel();` (guarded by __ANDROID__, mirroring the shared companionDs*() decl block — a
block-scope extern "C" is ill-formed, so it can't be function-local); hunk 2 adds the suppression in
updateVisible(), anchored on the unique `bool gameMode = !isGuiMode();` line (updateVisible runs at
the tail of push/popGuiMode, so the gate applies the moment GM_Travel is entered). Guarded by
!mGuiModes.empty() because getMode() reads mGuiModes.back().

Safety: TravelWindow commits travel only on an explicit destination tap (onTravelButtonClick) and
cancels via exit()/onCancelButtonClicked, never in onClose(), so hiding it on the visible->hidden
transition has no side effect. COMPANION_TRAVEL_CLOSED is emitted explicitly from every close path
(companion-travel-export.patch), covering the case where the window was already hidden so the
mode-pop's setVisible(false) is a no-op that never fires onClose().

--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -683,6 +683,14 @@
     extern "C" bool companionDsEnchanting();
     extern "C" bool companionDsAlchemy();
     extern "C" bool companionDsRestWait();
+#endif
+
+#ifdef __ANDROID__
+    // COMPANION: defined in androidmain.cpp (companion-travel-export.patch). True when Travel is in
+    // DS mode → the native GM_Travel window is suppressed in updateVisible() below. Declared in its
+    // own block (not the shared companionDs*() block above) so this travel patch stays self-contained.
+    // A block-scope extern "C" is ill-formed, so the declaration must live here at namespace scope.
+    extern "C" bool companionDsTravel();
 #endif
 
     void WindowManager::updateVisible()
@@ -864,6 +872,19 @@
                         modeWindow->setVisible(false);
         }
 
+        // COMPANION: hide the native travel destination window (GM_Travel) when Travel is in DS mode
+        // so the companion bottom screen is the sole travel surface; show it when Travel is Vanilla.
+        // TravelWindow is NOT a WindowManager member (there is no mTravelWindow) — like the six
+        // windows in the switch above it lives only in mGuiModeStates[GM_Travel].mWindows, so iterate
+        // those rather than a member setVisible(). It commits on an explicit tap (onTravelButtonClick)
+        // and only cancels via exit()/onCancel, so hiding on the visible->hidden transition is
+        // side-effect-free (COMPANION_TRAVEL_CLOSED is emitted explicitly from every close path in
+        // companion-travel-export.patch). companionDsTravel() is declared just above updateVisible().
+        if (!mGuiModes.empty() && getMode() == GM_Travel && companionDsTravel())
+            for (WindowBase* modeWindow : mGuiModeStates[GM_Travel].mWindows)
+                if (modeWindow)
+                    modeWindow->setVisible(false);
+
         bool gameMode = !isGuiMode();
 
         MWBase::Environment::get().getInputManager()->changeInputMode(!gameMode);
